description:
On this episode of ANN International: An Adventist hospital in Malawi celebrates the inauguration of a new open heart surgery facility.

Hundreds are baptized across Colombia during the Escrito Esta (It Is Written) Adventist evangelistic series.

The Adventist Church in Fiji collaborates with the Fijian government to address and combat diabetes in the region. 

Also, ADRA is chosen to lead a food resilience project in the Democratic Republic of Congo.

Stay tuned as ANN brings you these captivating stories and provides coverage of other global news. For a deeper dive into these headlines, visit adventist.news.

ANN is the official news channel of the Seventh-day Adventist Church.
